<DOC><DOCNO> AP880222-0147 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-02-22-88 1623EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i AM-BRF--WarCriminal     02-22 0154</FIRST><SECOND>AM-BRF--War Criminal,0157</SECOND><HEAD>Soviet Convicted Of Nazi Atrocities</HEAD><DATELINE>MOSCOW (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   A Soviet citizen was convicted of Nazi war crimesMonday and sentenced to 15 years in jail, the official news agencyreported.   Tass said Dmitri Maslo was found guilty of high treason andother charges after a trial in the mining town of Selidovo in theUkrainian republic.   During World War II, Maslo joined the police force in theUkrainian city of Krasnoarmeisk and ``voluntarily went over to theside of Nazi invaders,'' Tass said. It said he arrested andtortured Ukrainians and Jews and ``on many occasions he took partin the shooting of peaceful civilians.''   Maslo, who went on trial Feb. 9, also was accused of helpingkill prisoners in the Krasnoarmeisk jail in 1943 as Soviet forcesbegan liberating the area.   He fled when the Nazis withdrew and settled in Khristinovka,near the Ukrainian capital of Kiev, Tass said.</TEXT></DOC>